320,MosPAFC,2021-07-31,"Eat before arriving The hotel is perfectly situated for the terminal; the staff are great and the rooms are clean and comfortable for an overnight stay.  However, the quality of food for an evening meal is shocking, genuinely the worst I have ever experienced.  My 'beef' burger was grey or green - I really couldn't tell - but certainly a colour I have never seen before on anything edible.  The wedges soggy.  My wife's meal had coleslaw that had a crust which you broke through - think Ice Magic if you are old enough to remember.  So, definitely stay there for position and incredible convenience but eat before you get there."
